==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Remuneration
<hw>Re*mu`ner*a"tion</hw> <pr>(-?"sh?n)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>remuneratio</ets>: cf. F.
<ets>r⟦eacute⟧mun⟦eacute⟧ration</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>The act
of remunerating.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>That which is given to remunerate; an equivalent
given, as for services, loss, or sufferings.</def>
<rj><au>Shak.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><syn><b>Syn.</b> -- Reward; recompense; compensation; pay; payment;
repayment; satisfaction; requital.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Remunerative</ent>⟦br⟧
